\section{Regulatory conventions}{

ICH E3 specifies a \strong{3-part running header} on every table page:
\itemize{
\item \strong{Left zone}: Study/protocol identifier.
\item \strong{Center zone}: Compound name, document type, or left blank.
\item \strong{Right zone}: \code{"Page X of Y"}.
}

The \strong{database cutoff date} is a mandatory audit trail element. Standard
table shells show it on the right of the running header on every page:

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode">}}\preformatted{Study/Protocol: TFRM-2024-001          Database Cutoff Date: 31DEC2024
}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}

Implement this with:

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode r">}}\preformatted{fr_page(tokens = list(study = "TFRM-2024-001", cutoff = "31DEC2024")) |>
fr_pagehead(
  left  = "Study/Protocol: \{study\}",
  right = "Database Cutoff Date: \{cutoff\}"
)
}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}

Date format in RTF submissions is \code{DDMONYYYY} (e.g. \code{"31DEC2024"}), not
ISO 8601, to match SAS ODS date conventions.
}

\section{Spacing}{

By default, \strong{no gap} is inserted after the page header. Add one with
\code{\link[=fr_spacing]{fr_spacing()}}:

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode r">}}\preformatted{spec |> fr_spacing(pagehead_after = 1L)   # one blank line
spec |> fr_spacing(pagehead_after = 2L)   # two blank lines
}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}

This can also be set in \verb{_tlframe.yml}:

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode yaml">}}\preformatted{spacing:
  pagehead_after: 1
}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}

